    }), "I also recall the trip to Sis Joy & Bro Sam Okafor\u2019s wedding. To begin with, Miracle (our bus) in her bid to demonstrate her name developed some drama, so we got to the event late and a lot was dependent on Hallelujah Choir because Bro Sam was our Papa. (He took care of us, visiting us like we were his biological children \u2013 that\u2019s another story for another time; the Balewa experience with Bro Sam Okafor, Bro Obiora Ikeobi and Bro Frank Asieba). Anyway, we ministered during the reception at Onitsha. All Yoruba boys and girls singing Igbo songs \u201Clai wo we\u201D (off heart), your guess is as good as mine! Trust Bro Oby who was conducting the ministration (loving as anything but don\u2019t mess with him when duty calls, and unfortunately he is a perfectionist); he had to tell me and a few others \u201CMe cho nu\u201D, meaning shut up. Sis Bukky Olojede was leading that song since majority of us had been \u201Cme cho nued\u201D. So you kept dancing but you dared not sing those nonsense vocabularies that were making people laugh at us. I\u2019m sure you wonder what songs those were.", /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("br", {
