    }), "I felt I had \u201Cwasted\u201D too much time ignoring the Bible. I vividly remember my blue little King James Bible. I read that Bible like I had an exam; marked every \u201Cmarkable\u201D. In my second year I joined my Departmental politics and became the President of our the department (Nigeria Association of Computer Science Students -NACOSS). That was huge and demanding with all the attendant challenges inherited from past leaderships as I had to schedule my time to accommodate all I needed to do in Fellowship, studies and the department. And by God\u2019s grace we were able to set the standard and raise the dike. Back to my SCM story, I joined the Prayer Band unit.", /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("br", {
