    }), "I remember a day bro.LEKAN and I went.to.Lagos on this purpose. We just boarded a cab going to Ikeja from agege when someone close the door of the car on my finger that was hanging on the body of the car outside, imagine the sudden pain shout and cry, I thought all my fingers were gone. But when I came round and saw the five fingers were still on my hand even though I\u2019ve to bear with the pain for dome days I was so.happy and gave glory to God. Emmanuel college of Theology was our hide out, our secret place  for prayer and fasting. Sometimes three days and night of continued fellowship and praising God. There was true holy love among us and no wonder the fellowship exploded during this time.", /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("br", {
